WHO   — Exponential Growth — Malthus's alarm · dN/dt = rN
WHAT  — The naive baseline and the original alarm (Malthus, 1798): unlimited growth against a limited world.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because the whole field begins by noticing that nothing grows exponentially forever.
HOW   — By compounding at rate r until resources, predators, or disease bend the curve.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Left alone I double and double and double. Nothing alive gets to keep me — the world always says no.

